The above camera models are solved for each zoom position using a least-square minimization of dot target locations in the geometric dataset. The OpenCV pure-photogrammetric solutions for focal length and field-of-view (FOV) are given in Fig. 35(a) and 35(b). The focal lengths for the left and right Mastcam-Z’s differ by less than 0.1% at a given zoom position, and vary linearly with zoom motor-count after about 1800 motor-counts. The discontinuity between 26 mm and 34 mm is to protect the launch-lock position at 26 mm. In actuality, the transition is more gradual than depicted in Fig. 35(a). The mapping between focal length and zoom position is given as 23FL(l)={0.01054×l+8.77if l>200026.16if l<600\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
