				\begin{document}$0< l<200$\end{document}, which should be avoided in-flight. As a result, 26 mm images can be taken at either 0 mc or between 200 mc and 600 mc with only minor changes of principal-point that can be readily corrected. More importantly, the focal length does not measurably change for l≤600\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
