				\begin{document}$l \leq 600$\end{document}.

Fig. 35(c,d) shows the zoom dependence of the stereo baseline and toe-in angles, respectively. The stereo-baseline between the left and right cameraheads varies by less than 2 mm over the entire zoom range. Toe-in, defined as the half angle between the rays passing through the center pixels of the left and right cameraheads, is similarly stable across zoom with a variance of less than 0.2∘\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
				\usepackage{amsmath}
				\usepackage{wasysym}
