The principal points (Fig. 35(g,h)) can be interpreted as the location (i.e., pixel) on the detector array that intersect each camerahead’s optical axis. The observed column and row values for the principal point vary by ±200 pixels across the entirety of the zoom range. Note that the disagreement between the OpenCV and CAHVOR principal points at 110 mm seen in Fig. 35(h) are not significant, as the CAHVOR solution uses the distortion term for the optical axis O\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
